---
<article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">July 12, 2026</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">Copywriting follow-up to the same-day conversion pass, addressing two items it flagged.</p>
  <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
    <li><strong>Homepage H1 reframed:</strong> the second line changed from "A Trusted Marketplace for Everyone" to "A Marketplace Backed by Real Data." The prior wording had BreederHQ asserting trust in its own voice, which sits too close to the identity-and-credentials posture (BreederHQ does not verify, vet, or vouch). The new line states the mechanism (listings backed by real program data) that lets buyers judge for themselves, and mirrors the "How it connects" section directly below it.</li>
    <li><strong>Pricing fee tables simplified:</strong> the "Marketplace Listing Fees" section now leads with the plain-language promise ("No percentage of your sales. No commission. No broker in the middle. You run your own transactions and keep every dollar of your deals.") instead of ending with it as a footnote. The detailed fee table and the optional-upgrades table are now collapsed behind disclosure toggles ("See the full fee schedule" and "See optional upgrade pricing"), removing a wall of struck-through prices from the default view at the moment of decision while keeping every number one click away.</li>
  </ul>
</article>
